Aim: To Install Node.js on the system and verify its successful installation using the Command Prompt/Terminal.
Steps
1. Open a web browser and go to the official Node.js website:
https://nodejs.org/en/download & on the homepage, download the LTS (Long-Term Support) version of Node.js suitable for your operating system.
2. Once the installer is downloaded, double-click on it to start the installation & Follow the installation wizard:











 
1.	Click Next













2. Accept the Terms of license and do Next












 
3. Select the destination folder













4. Select the custom setup and do Next












5. Now ready to download the Node.js



6. Wait until the installation is completed, then click Finish.


Prompt / Terminal to verify installation & Type the following commands to check the version :

•	node -v → Displays Node.js version
•	npm -v → Displays npm (Node Package Manager) version
 









 
